<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Dive" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Dive,</orth> to plunge or sink in a fluid: <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.191" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 191</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.2.139" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 2, 139</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.203" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 203</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.3.43" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 3, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 1, 2</bibl>. Per. <bibl n="shak. tim 3.0." default="NO" valid="yes">III Prol. 49</bibl>. Figuratively: <cit><quote>to d. into their hearts,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.4.25" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 4, 25</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>d., thoughts, down to my soul,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.41" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 1, 41</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>hath not yet --d into the world's deceit,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.8" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 8</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he --s into the king's soul, and there scatters dangers, doubts,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 2.2.27" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 2, 27</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>